<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="123" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">831.00/1–449: Circular telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in
                                    the American Republics, Except Cuba and Venezuela</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-04">January 4,
                                1949</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Embassy Habana reports that prior to leaving Habana Jan 3 for visit in
                            Miami Gallegos told press he had received from State Dept completely
                            satisfactory explanation activities US in Caracas.</p>
                        <p>Gallegos by this act has publicly confirmed what he stated privately some
                            time ago, namely his recognition that charges of US involvement in Venez
                            coup are completely false.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>